(Atho SegWit Sizing and Throughput Reference) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Date: 2026-04-10) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This document describes the active Atho sizing model for transaction weight, virtual size) Tj
T*
(\(vsize\), and throughput estimation. It is intended for node operators, wallet/API integrators,) Tj
T*
(and reviewers validating fee/tps assumptions.) Tj
T*
(- Active Sizing Limits) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(From Src/Utility/const.py:) Tj
T*
(- MAX_BLOCK_SIZE_BYTES = 3,500,000) Tj
T*
(- MAX_BLOCK_WEIGHT = 14,000,000) Tj
T*
(- MAX_TRANSACTION_SIZE_BYTES = 250,000 \(policy vsize cap\)) Tj
T*
(- WITNESS_SCALE_FACTOR = 4) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(These values establish the hard envelope for mempool admission and block packing. Any throughput) Tj
T*
(estimate that ignores these limits is not aligned with current consensus policy.) Tj
T*
(- Canonical Metric Definitions) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Atho uses SegWit-style accounting:) Tj
T*
(- weight = base_bytes * 3 + total_bytes) Tj
T*
(- vsize = ceil\(weight / 4\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Interpretation:) Tj
T*
(- base bytes are weighted heavier,) Tj
T*
(- witness bytes are discounted relative to base,) Tj
T*
(- fee policy and packing policy are both driven by vsize.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Current fee baseline tied to vsize:) Tj
T*
(- fee floor 350 atoms/vB,) Tj
T*
(- minimum fee 100,000 atoms.) Tj
T*
(- Base vs Witness Counting Rules) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Base view \(no-witness form\):) Tj
T*
(- remove top-level witness fields,) Tj
T*
(- blank script_sig in input entries for deterministic no-witness sizing.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Total view:) Tj
T*
(- includes witness payload and all fields.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Implementation references:) Tj
T*
(- Src/SigWit/sigwit.py::SegWit.sizes_bytes) Tj
T*
(- binary tx serialization paths when available \(ATX2 transport\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The important point is deterministic counting, not ad-hoc JSON length heuristics.) Tj
T*
(- Throughput Formula) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Let:) Tj
T*
(- Bv = 3,500,000 effective vbytes per block,) Tj
T*
(- T = 120 seconds per block target,) Tj
T*
(- F = packing factor \(1.0 ideal, 0.95 conservative\),) Tj
T*
(- Savg = average non-coinbase tx vsize.) Tj
T*
ET
endstream
endobj
